subsection.p:
Now integrate around the unit circle: x=\cos t,\qquad y=\sin t,\qquad 0\le t\le2\pi. Then dx=-\sin t\,dt, \qquad dy=\cos t\,dt, and x^2+y^2=1. Therefore
\omega \amp = -\sin t(-\sin t\,dt)+\cos t(\cos t\,dt) \amp = dt.
So \boxed{\oint_C\omega=2\pi.}

