subsection.p:
      Your task.
      Choose one orientation-sensitive problem and compute it twice: once correctly and once
      with a common orientation error. Use one of these.

\begin{array}{c|c}
\text{Problem} \amp \text{Common sign error} \\ \hline
\text{annulus area from } \eta=\frac12(x\,dy-y\,dx)
\amp
\text{inner boundary walked counterclockwise}\\[1mm]
\text{flux through a closed box}
\amp
\text{one face normal points inward}\\[1mm]
\text{Stokes' theorem on a disk}
\amp
\text{boundary direction disagrees with normal}\\[1mm]
\text{surface integral over a parametrized surface}
\amp
\text{parameters swapped}\\[1mm]
\text{Green's theorem on a rectangle}
\amp
\text{boundary walked clockwise}
\end{array}

      Orientation checklist.
      Use this checklist in your report.

\begin{array}{c|l}
\text{Object} \amp \text{Positive orientation rule} \\ \hline
\text{interval} \amp \text{right endpoint positive, left endpoint negative}\\[1mm]
\text{plane region} \amp \text{walk so the region stays on the left}\\[1mm]
\text{surface in space} \amp \text{right-hand rule connects normal and boundary}\\[1mm]
\text{solid} \amp \text{boundary surface points outward}\\[1mm]
\text{parametrized surface} \amp \mathbf r_u\times\mathbf r_v \text{ gives the chosen normal}
\end{array}
